quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,95,"Indeed, Allah is the Splitter of the grain and the fruit stone. He brings out the living from the dead{1}, and<i>(He is) </i>the Bringer Out of the dead from the living{2}. Such is Allah, so how can you<sup>pl </sup>be averted<i>(from the truth) </i>?",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift in Arabic from a nominal sentence to a verbal sentence.],footnotes:2:[A grammatical shift in Arabic from a verbal sentence to a nominal sentence.]
  6,96,"<i>(He is) </i>the Splitter of the daybreak, and He has made{1}the night for rest and the sun and the moon for calculation; such is the determining of the Almighty, the All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…and the Maker of the night (as a time) for rest…”]
  6,97,"And it is He Who made for you the stars, that you may be guided by them in the darkness<i>(es) </i>of land and sea. Surely, We{1}have detailed the signs for people who know.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.]
  6,98,"And it is He Who initiated you from a single self, then a place of settlement{1}and a storage. Surely, We<sup>a </sup>have detailed the signs for people who comprehend.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Rouh read it as: “…then a settled one and a stored one.”],footnotes:2:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup> person to 1 person to 1<sup>st</sup> person. person.]
  6,99,"And it is He who sent down water from the sky, and with it We<sup>a </sup>brought out the germination of everything, then We brought out from it greenery from which We bring out{1}layered grain. And out of the palm-trees—from their spathes— clusters of dates, hanging low, and gardens of grapevines, and the olives, and the pomegranates—similar{2}yet dissimilar{3}. Look at its produce when it has yielded its produce and<i>(look at) </i>its ripening. Most surely in that are signs for people who believe.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup>],footnotes:2:[person to 1 person],footnotes:3:[to 1<sup>st</sup> person. person.]
  6,100,"Yet they made for Allah associates—the unseen beings{1}—although He created them, and they invented{2}for Him sons and daughters, without<i>(any) </i>knowledge. Highly Exalted is He and Most High, far above what they describe.",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “...and they kept inventing for Him sons and daughters,”]
  6,101,"Originator of the heavens and the earth—how can He have offspring when He never had a consort? And He created everything, and He is All-Knowing of everything."
